JLPT levels don't mean anything
you should just study the language and consider maybe taking the N2 or N1 once you're at an intermediate or advanced intermediate level
even once you've passed N1 it doesn't really mean anything, there will be lots of stuff you don't know
and N2 is usually where people start to think you must've "gotten good" but the truth is that it's baby level and means maybe you can read easy manga but your Japanese is probably still shit and you will sound like a retard any time you open your mouth
putting a lot of effort into things like N4 or 3 is like going to a driving classroom or something where you learn about road rules but never actually get into a car
there is literally no one who cares about those things except maybe learning institutions trying to make money off you by selling certifications

just focus on learning more than you currently know

Alright /med/, so I am going to make a good /int/ post for once. I am going to share with you a recipe from a drink/snack that is traditionally consumed during Christmas, particularly after the midnight Christmas mass. In fact I've heard of churches/monasteries serving it to the congregation after the mass is over. This year will be the first year where I'll be tasting it. Here's the recipe

Imbuljuta tal-Qastan

400g dried chestnuts
A lemon's rind
A tangerine's rind
200g sugar
Half a teaspoon of mixed spice
A teaspoon of cloves
100g of chocolate powder

Put the chestnuts in water and leave them overnight.
Remove any remaining shells.
Put the chestnuts - along with the rest of the ingredients - in a saucepan.
Drown them in water.
Cover the saucepan and let the water reach boiling point.
Lower the heat and let it simmer for around 2 hours until the chestnuts are well-cooked.
From time to time you have to add some warm water due to evaporation.

Can be served either hot or cold.

The chestnuts are consumed, hence the "drink/snack" descriptor.

>The capital of the Hittite Empire was Hattusas.
O šêrutno le Hittitesko Amperetsija sas Hattusas.
O baro gav la Hittitesko Amperetsija sas Hattusas.

The Romani Wikipedia writes "the capital city" as "o sherutno foro" but I texted my grandma and she said it should be "o baro gav. I think in proper orthography it should be written "šêrutno" but if my memory serves me correct a "šêrutno" is like a person who is your boss or foreman at work. "baro" just means "big" in Romani, and "gav" is town/village, so I'm not sure which one to use here. As for "foro" I'm pretty sure it's from Romanian "afară" meaning "outside" since Gypsies usually lived outside the cities. I prefer the term "gav".

for "le Hittitesko" vs "la Hittitesko" depends on if it's a feminine or masucline noun. "La [noun]-ko/-esko" is the genitive marker for feminine, and "Le [noun]-ko/-esko" is the masculine.

>Troy was a real city.
E Troy sas jekh čačo gav.

I'm not sure why, but the definite article "e" just feels right with the word "Troy", it's just a feeling thing for me. "sas" is just the past tense of "to be" which in the present tense is "si".

"čačo" is a really cool word I like a lot, and it has many uses in Romani. It was inherited from Sauraseni Prakrit 𑀲𑀘𑁆𑀘 (sacca), from Ashokan Prakrit 𑀲𑀘 (saca), from Sanskrit सत्य (satya, “true”). Cognates include Hindi सच्चा (saccā, “true”).

>Where were those Luwians going?
Kai gêlé kodole Luvie (not sure how to write this properly but I did my best)?

It more or less directly translates to "Where (they) went those Luvies?"

>>175215386
There's the idea of the "silent period" in language acquisition, but I don't think it's 2 years long.
It is true that some adult learners who force themselves to speak will create bad habits, but I think that's just because some adults are less willing to change than children. A child born in America who moves to England at age 7 is much more likely to change their accent than an adult.
But I don't think that it's bad to make mistakes in your TL as long as you don't let those mistakes become habits. Children will pronounce things wrong and make grammar errors for years, and it doesn't permanently damage their language ability. Because they're actively trying to improve. A child might struggle with the "r" sound for months before they develop the motor skills to pronounce it properly. If as an adult you don't allow yourself to get comfortable being "good enough" I don't see any problem with outputting 3 words sentences very early. I see no reason for you to wait 2 years to say "Je suis grand"

I can't tell you about specific papers, but there's a famous lecture of Stephen Krashen where he says, contrary to his expectations, research shows that output doesn't do shit and speaking is not practice. Talking to people helps but this is because the person you're talking will often lower their speech to your level and give you comprehensible input through the conversation. Just talking out loud in your car is not going to do much.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NiTsduRreug

Speaking is something that emerges out of you once you acquire enough words and an intuitive sense for the language. You really don't need to be talking to yourself, saying simple sentences, if you're already reading and listening a lot. Two years is probably too much, but it depends on how much you've acquired, someone could reach that level in 6 months or less if they're motivated.

I'm two months into German and haven't tried speaking at all, except the occasional word that sounds cool to yell around the house. I just read and learn vocab, look up grammar when I'm confused about something and that's it. I don't even do the writing challenges here because I don't see the point in it.

I remember for English, I never really practiced speaking or grammar, just watched tons of cartoons and played on the computer. By the time I was in 5th grade, I was pretty much fluent. I couldn't tell you what a Past Perfect tense was or other grammar structures, but I could use it and know when it's wrong simply "by ear". Which is the kind of intuition everyone should be aiming for. You don't want to consciously think, oh shit, is the object or the time or the adjective suppose to come first, when you're trying to express some kind of thought in a conversation. I guess if you really need to get by in a foreign country, even Tarzan level speech will help or just pointing.

>>175221916
Research seems to say it doesn't matter. Output probably won't hurt, but if it requires lots of time and effort, which you're probably better of just using to read a book or listen to something comprehensible. If you're planning on learning 2 or 3 languages, then it helps to think about what truly makes a difference and what you can safely avoid.

It sounds shocking because everyone knows you need to speak to learn a language, but it turns out it's just one of those memes that isn't true when you study it under a microscope.

Well, if you're outputting, then presumably you want it to be correct, right? So in order to know if it's correct, without the intuition of a lot of input, you have to look up the rules, learn them consciously and practice applying them when writing. The exercise boils down to practicing grammar rules, which will help you on a test where you have time to think and "monitor" yourself, but you won't reach fluency if you're still thinking about the rules. Every time I reach for a word, it's going to already be there and the grammar will be correct because it will sound correct to me without even knowing the definition of the rule.

The first dude is happy with the level he's reached and he decides to begin outputting and does so by shadowing whilst continuing to engage passively with his TL. Findus Jultallrik - En historia om ensamhet

Jan hade just vaknat. Han drog sin grova hand genom sin 5-dagars skäggstubb. Det skulle kännas skönt att få raka sig tänkte Jan, men samtidigt visste han att pengarna kunde gå till viktigare saker. En av dom sakerna var att köpa en julklapp till sin 15-åriga dotter.

Förra julen hade det skitit sig. Jan hade krökat till hos några av sina dryckeskamrater från Lilla Monaco i Blackeberg och däckat. När han vaknade upp så upptäckte han att plånboken var försvunnen. Han förbannade sig själv och hällde upp ett glas brännvin för att lugna ner sig.

Brännvinet var det enda i Jans liv som aldrig tog slut. Han köpte alltid ett par dunkar hembrännt, och när bidraget kom så firade han med att gå till systemet och köpa två flaskor Explorer vodka och några Pripps blå. Aldrig att han skulle vara utan.

Han satte på tv-n och möttes av den där blyga tjuren i Kalles Ankas julafton. Jävlar, tänkte Jan. Det är ju julafton. Det Jan gjorde i denna stund var att ringa till hem till sin ex-fru där hans dotter bodde. Jan hade förr i tiden varit områdeschef på Skanska och hade tjänat riktigt bra. Han hade bott i ett fint hus i Södra Ängby tillsammans med sin fru. Dom fick tillsammans en pojke och en flicka.

Livet var en dans på rosor. Men deras son dog. En bil hade nere vid Islandstorget släckt hans sons liv. Efter det så började det gå ut för. Sorgarbetet och ilskan dämpades hos Jan med stora mängder sprit. På arbetsplatsen försökte dom hjälpa honom så mycket som möjligt. Men till slut var det försent.

Jan blev uppsagd från sitt arbete. Det blev skilsmässa. Vårdnaden av dottern gick till mamman. Nu bodde Jan i en 1:a i Vällingby.

posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com:
Quando addentate una patatina fritta di McDonald's, non state semplicemente mangiando delle patate cotte. State sperimentando una performance culinaria complessa e multimilionaria che si avvale delle migliori scienze alimentari del mondo e che mira a coinvolgere tutti i vostri sensi, dall'olfatto (aroma di sego di manzo) al gusto (perfetto equilibrio di zuccheri, grassi e sale) alla vista (forma e colore ideali), fino al tatto e al suono (che contribuiscono entrambi alla sensazione in bocca).

Ogni aspetto della vostra esperienza è stato attentamente studiato, testato e analizzato da ricercatori e psicologi. È stato anche sottoposto a un'analisi di milioni di dollari di attrezzature all'avanguardia, molte delle quali costruite su misura per l'industria del fast food.

Certo, l'obiettivo finale è quello di vendere più patatine fritte. E io rispondo: "E allora?". Questo non oscura la bellezza del fatto che così tanto pensiero, sforzo e intenzione siano stati impiegati nella creazione di un'esperienza apparentemente semplice e quotidiana.

Le opere di Shakespeare erano, ai loro tempi, l'intrattenimento commerciale delle masse, intriso di birra e scialbo. Oggi sono considerate le più grandi opere mai create in lingua inglese. Sono in qualche modo offuscate dal fatto di essere state scritte per un pubblico pagante, o di essere state apprezzate dalle masse e non da un'élite di alto livello?

Buonasera, scrivo qui perché ho bisogno di consigli e non so a chi altro rivolgermi. Parto col dire che sono una persona molto riservata e timida e come conseguenza ho sempre avuto grandi difficoltà a fare amicizia. Durante la pandemia (proprio nel periodo del primissimo lockdown) mi sono trovata quasi per caso in un canale Discord in cui ho incontrato gente simpaticissima. Abbiamo iniziato giocando insieme, poi con alcune di queste persone è nato qualcosa di più e siamo arrivati anche a parlare in privato tutti i giorni. Mi sono sentita capita sotto molto punti di vista come raramente mi era successo nella vita reale. Non è che io abbia sempre incontrato brutte persone irl, ma essendo, come ho detto, una persona estremamente timida, incontravo parecchie difficoltà nel socializzare.

Comunque, con queste persone stava andando tutto bene finché, a ottobre, non ho avuto una ricaduta: sono tornata a soffrire di quella depressione che non ti fa uscire nemmeno dal letto, e praticamente da inizio novembre sono sparita, mi sono presa una pausa generale dai social. Ora che sto meglio e vorrei riprendere i contatti, mi sento tremendamente in colpa a farlo. Le persone con cui parlavo più spesso sapevano già che la mia salute mentale non fosse proprio al top, ma il fatto è che sono sparita così, da un giorno all'altro, e ora vorrei solo essere onestà e dire semplicemente che è stato un periodo nero, ma ho il timore che ora mi odino, o che sia passato troppo tempo e che ormai sia "fuori".

Adesso ho realizzato che ogni volta che faccio tardi e bevo/fumo sto prendendo in prestito energia dal giorno successivo. Nel senso che il giorno dopo avrò nebbia mentale e un lieve stato depressivo.

È l’articolo che stavo aspettando, forse tra i più lampanti esempi di redpill e anche quello di più difficile comprensione: il mondo varia in base a come veniamo percepiti ed è davvero difficile percepirsi in modo oggettivo.
Da ragazzo non me ne rendevo conto, anzi, convinto com’ero ai tempi di essere anche molto carino, non capivo proprio perché il mio atteggiamento rilassato e fascinoso (così credevo) non desse i risultati sperati.
Una delle prime volte in cui mi resi conto di quanto fosse influente l’aspetto fisico fu quando mi ritrovai a camminare per le vie del centro con una mia ex collega. Ragazza bionda, occhi verdi, seno sulla quarta, non tanto alta ma con un bel fisico tonico.
Fu come se si fossero accesi i riflettori su di lei e di conseguenza anche su di me: gli uomini la squadravano con il tipico occhio pallato italico, ma ciò che mi stupì furono le donne. Quasi tutte la osservavano da capo a piedi e poi buttavano un occhio su di me, come a valutare secondariamente come fosse il suo ipotetico compagno.
Le stesse vie, percorse svariate volte da solo, non mi avevano mai dato alcun feedback.
